---
Manage plugins (Sprint 7 §2)

Usage: plugins <COMMAND>

Commands:
  list     List every discovered plugin (name, kind, version, enabled)
  inspect  Inspect a single plugin manifest by `(kind, name)`
  enable   Enable a plugin (persisted enabled-state lands in §3 follow-on)
  disable  Disable a plugin
  install  Install a plugin from a manifest file. Copies the plugin directory into the user
           discovery root and prompts for the declared cap grant
  help     Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
  -h, --help
          Print help
